From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 10:29:30 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 51/51] inline-3d: fix vertical squish of 2D overlays (raster
 padding sampled as content)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Every DP-composited 2D overlay was vertically squished, badly for short/wide
elements (a sticky header bar) and imperceptibly for tall ones. Distinct from the
fixed browser#29 2x blow-up — this is a permanent Y-compression.

Root cause, measured with a per-overlay VLOG on hardware: the isolated-layer
raster (overlay_img) is allocated with GPU tile-alignment PADDING — width rounded
up to a multiple of 32, HEIGHT to a multiple of 64. A 3844x140 header bar rasters
into a 3872x192 image; a 750x750 square into 768x768. The element content sits 1:1
in the top-left, the extra right/bottom texels are empty.

The overlay-atlas draw computed sy = overlay_img->height()/full.height() (= 192/140
= 1.371) and sampled the WHOLE padded image into the content-height dst, crushing
the real 140px of content into 140*140/192 ~= 73% height. On a 750px square the
ratio is 750/768 ~= 98%, invisible — which is exactly why wide-short bars squished
while a 300px square looked perfect.

Fix: the raster is the content at device scale plus padding, not a stretched copy
of |full|, so sample the content region at SCALE 1 keyed off |full| and let the
kStrict clamp exclude the padding. Clipped overlays (browser#18 bug B) still take
only their visible fraction (r - full), now without the bogus img/full scale.

HW-validated on Leia: the overlay-aspect-test probe matrix (full-width top/mid bars,
narrow bars, 300px square — inscribed circles) went from P1-P4 squished / P5 fine to
all round. David: "FIXED".
---
 .../skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc        | 31 ++++++++++++-------
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/components/viz/service/display_embedder/skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc b/components/viz/service/display_embedder/skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc
index 79265d9318de0..cd0bd9016cfc8 100644
--- a/components/viz/service/display_embedder/skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc
+++ b/components/viz/service/display_embedder/skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc
@@ -3358,17 +3358,26 @@ void SkiaOutputSurfaceImplOnGpu::WeaveCompositedSurface(SkSurface* output,
           // fix bug B applied to the canvas path: key off the unclipped rect and
           // take the matching fraction of the source.
           const gfx::Rect full = overlay.rect;
-          const float sx = full.width() > 0
-                               ? static_cast<float>(overlay_img->width()) /
-                                     static_cast<float>(full.width())
-                               : 1.0f;
-          const float sy = full.height() > 0
-                               ? static_cast<float>(overlay_img->height()) /
-                                     static_cast<float>(full.height())
-                               : 1.0f;
-          const SkRect src =
-              SkRect::MakeXYWH((r.x() - full.x()) * sx, (r.y() - full.y()) * sy,
-                               r.width() * sx, r.height() * sy);
+          // The isolated-layer raster (overlay_img) is allocated with GPU
+          // tile-alignment PADDING — its width is rounded up to a multiple of 32
+          // and its HEIGHT to a multiple of 64 (measured: a 3844x140 bar → a
+          // 3872x192 image, a 750x750 square → 768x768). The element's content
+          // sits 1:1 in the TOP-LEFT of that image; the extra right/bottom texels
+          // are empty. So the raster is the content at device scale plus padding,
+          // NOT a stretched copy of |full|.
+          //
+          // Therefore sample the content region at SCALE 1, keyed off |full|, and
+          // let kStrict clamp keep the empty padding out. The earlier code scaled
+          // the source by overlay_img/full and thereby pulled the padding into
+          // |dst|, vertically SQUISHING every overlay by content/allocated —
+          // catastrophic for short elements (a 140px bar crushed into 140*140/192
+          // ≈ 73% height) and ~invisible for tall ones (750/768 ≈ 98%), which is
+          // exactly why wide-short bars squished while a 300px square did not
+          // (browser#29-Y). r ⊆ full, so (r − full) is the visible sub-rect of the
+          // content and maps 1:1 into |dst|; a clipped overlay (browser#18 bug B)
+          // still takes only its visible fraction, just without the bogus scale.
+          const SkRect src = SkRect::MakeXYWH(r.x() - full.x(), r.y() - full.y(),
+                                              r.width(), r.height());
           const SkRect dst =
               SkRect::MakeXYWH(r.x(), r.y(), r.width(), r.height());
           atlas_surface->getCanvas()->drawImageRect(
